diff --git a/CONTRIBUTING.md b/CONTRIBUTING.md
index fef6cb217add0b41244decf439b234d686991e6d..a57cf78a9a74bbd77b1008b2972451bb59e07364 100644
--- a/CONTRIBUTING.md
+++ b/CONTRIBUTING.md
@@ -277,3 +277,7 @@
 Be sure to select the correct target branch; the default is `master`, so if you're contributing a change to a different version, switch it to that version's branch, e.g. `gnome-50`. Fill out the merge request description (it might be helpful to look at [recently merged MRs](https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-build-meta/-/merge_requests/?sort=created_date&state=merged&first_page_size=20) for inspiration), submit it, and someone will review it for you.
 
 Once approved, CI/CD will build your MR and run the automated integration tests to make sure nothing breaks.
+
+## 10. What happens after your changes are merged
+
+Once your changes have landed in the `gnome-build-meta` repository, either directly or via an upstream release picked up by [`update_refs`](.gitlab-ci.yml), CI/CD will build and deploy new prebuilt images and update the sysupdate repository. You can then upgrade to the latest version using GNOME Software, `updatectl`, or by installing the latest prebuilt image.

